attributes.additional_details:
This will: 
-reduce burden of rail commuters;
-encourage people to commute - increase mobility, ease housing issue in London and other major cities;
-develop surrounding towns and cities of major cities;
-reduce driving to work - less air and noise pollution;
-more 1st class take up rate.
-more commuters - increase income for railway companies, which can then lower the rail price. 
-lesser road maintenance and rail subsidies for government.

Steps to prevent mis-use should also be considered.
